cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.CL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper investigates the spread of emotions in online social media and their relation to social networks. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper uses computational methods to analyze millions of tweets. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as the paper discusses the implications of the findings for personal anger management and controlling collective outrage in cyberspace. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is relevant as the paper investigates the spread of emotions in social networks. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses natural language processing techniques to analyze the tweets.
